From: adopt@CAM.ORG (Richard Migneron)
Subject: Serial Ports - How to Configure !!!!
Date: 24 Oct 1993 10:23:53 -0400

Hello all,

        I have a simple question Today : First, I finally finished
installing the full blown SLS Release (all 29 diskettes worth).

        Now, I have an internal modem in COM3 with IRQ5.  Now the
default Linux config, tells me that it is in IRQ4.  I search the MAN 8
directory, and found a nice little command named SETSERIAL, which tells
me that I can reconfigure all my ports to whatever I feel like.

        The big trouble is that this command is nowhere to be found !!!
It is not in /etc like man says, and whereis doesn't find it.

        Q: Where is it really, if not in /etc ?

        Q: In what package is it on the SLS release, so that I can
           re-install it, or re-get the faulty or missing package ?

        Q: Is there another way to reconfig the Serial ports ?

Thanks for the time you will take to answer this, I will really
appreciate it (I might just finally destroy my DOS/Windows environnement
if I get to call on my modem, so HHHHHEEEELLLLPPP !!!!)

-Richard

