From: jon@Armstrong.EDU (Jon Wright)
Subject: Re: Linux with 2 Ethernet Cards
Date: Sun, 24 Oct 1993 18:05:18 GMT

 Well, I was looking into doing this. There is a reference to it in either the
Ethernet or Net-2 Howto( Don't remember which off of the top of my head, sorry).
What I had to do to get my machine to recognize both cards, Elite 16 Combos, 
was to boot from lilo w/ the following arguments :

boot: linux ether=15,0x280,0xcc000,0,eth0 ether=5,0x300,0xd0000,0,eth1

 This tells my machine exactly where the cards are and lets me work with 
both of them. I was having a problem trying to compile this information into the
kernel using variables, so I just added the eth1 device in space.c and specify
at boot time. Can someone tell me how to put these arguments into a lilo
configuration file so that I don't have to type them when the machine reboots ?


 Jon

