From: marcb@netcom.com (Marc Bernstein)
Subject: Re: How Do I make a boot disk?
Date: Sun, 24 Oct 1993 19:18:56 GMT

Don Van Drei (dvandrei@gadfly.lerc.nasa.gov) wrote:
:       I've corrupted my floppy boot disk and need to make a new one,
: what is the command?  I've installed a, b, and c, but don't know where
: the command makebootdisk is.  Also it states that to created a boot on
: my harddrive I can 'play with /usr/src/lilo', well that doesn't exist 
: either.
: -- 
: -----------------------------------------------------
: Donald Van Drei            NASA Lewis Research Center
: dvandrei@gadfly.lerc.nasa.gov          (216) 433-9089 
: -----------------------------------------------------

I just wnet through this and will help as best I can.

If you have your a1.3 disk, still. Try the following. Boot off of it.
After logging in as root, do 'doinstall /dev/hda (or whatever device has the
boot sector). Now when it asks where you are installing from pick 'tape'.
Then pick floppies as your destination. Voila! 

Good luck!

PS when you said you corrupted your boot floppy you weren't talking about your
a1.3 disk were you?

